# Padroes de Teste Vue (Vue Test Utils)

## Estrutura Base

```ts
import { mount } from "@vue/test-utils";
import Button from "./Button.vue";

describe("Button", () => {
  it("renderiza com texto do slot", () => {
    const wrapper = mount(Button, {
      slots: { default: "Salvar" },
    });
    expect(wrapper.text()).toContain("Salvar");
  });

  it("emite click ao clicar", async () => {
    const wrapper = mount(Button);
    await wrapper.find("button").trigger("click");
    expect(wrapper.emitted("click")).toHaveLength(1);
  });
});
```

## mount vs shallowMount

```ts
// mount — renderiza componentes filhos (integracao)
const wrapper = mount(UserCard, {
  props: { user: mockUser },
});

// shallowMount — stubs componentes filhos (unitario)
const wrapper = shallowMount(UserCard, {
  props: { user: mockUser },
});
```

## Props e Emits

```ts
it("aplica variante via prop", () => {
  const wrapper = mount(Button, {
    props: { variant: "outline" },
  });
  expect(wrapper.classes()).toContain("btn--outline");
});

it("emite update com valor correto", async () => {
  const wrapper = mount(Input);
  await wrapper.find("input").setValue("teste");
  expect(wrapper.emitted("update:modelValue")?.[0]).toEqual(["teste"]);
});
```

## Async e nextTick

```ts
import { nextTick } from "vue";

it("atualiza DOM apos mudanca de estado", async () => {
  const wrapper = mount(Counter);
  await wrapper.find("button").trigger("click");
  await nextTick();
  expect(wrapper.find(".count").text()).toBe("1");
});
```

## Plugins e Provide

```ts
const wrapper = mount(Component, {
  global: {
    plugins: [router, pinia],
    provide: { theme: "dark" },
    stubs: { Teleport: true },
  },
});
```

## Convencoes

- Preferir `mount` para testes de integracao
- Usar `shallowMount` para testes unitarios isolados
- Verificar emits via `wrapper.emitted()`
- Sempre usar `await` com `trigger` e `setValue`
- Usar `nextTick` quando necessario aguardar reatividade
