# Vue Testing Patterns (Vue Test Utils)

## Base Structure

```ts
import { mount } from "@vue/test-utils";
import Button from "./Button.vue";

describe("Button", () => {
  it("renders with slot text", () => {
    const wrapper = mount(Button, {
      slots: { default: "Save" },
    });
    expect(wrapper.text()).toContain("Save");
  });

  it("emits click when clicked", async () => {
    const wrapper = mount(Button);
    await wrapper.find("button").trigger("click");
    expect(wrapper.emitted("click")).toHaveLength(1);
  });
});
```

## mount vs shallowMount

```ts
// mount — renders child components (integration)
const wrapper = mount(UserCard, {
  props: { user: mockUser },
});

// shallowMount — stubs child components (unit)
const wrapper = shallowMount(UserCard, {
  props: { user: mockUser },
});
```

## Props and Emits

```ts
it("applies variant via prop", () => {
  const wrapper = mount(Button, {
    props: { variant: "outline" },
  });
  expect(wrapper.classes()).toContain("btn--outline");
});

it("emits update with correct value", async () => {
  const wrapper = mount(Input);
  await wrapper.find("input").setValue("test");
  expect(wrapper.emitted("update:modelValue")?.[0]).toEqual(["test"]);
});
```

## Async and nextTick

```ts
import { nextTick } from "vue";

it("updates DOM after state change", async () => {
  const wrapper = mount(Counter);
  await wrapper.find("button").trigger("click");
  await nextTick();
  expect(wrapper.find(".count").text()).toBe("1");
});
```

## Plugins and Provide

```ts
const wrapper = mount(Component, {
  global: {
    plugins: [router, pinia],
    provide: { theme: "dark" },
    stubs: { Teleport: true },
  },
});
```

## Conventions

- Prefer `mount` for integration tests
- Use `shallowMount` for isolated unit tests
- Check emits via `wrapper.emitted()`
- Always `await` with `trigger` and `setValue`
- Use `nextTick` when waiting for reactivity updates
